Figs. 5A and 5B show perspective views from below and above, respectively, of the connector plate which is used to connect to the vehicle body frame;
Fig. 6 shows a perspective view from the side of the tilt frame, mounted at the rear of the chassis frame, which is used to provide a smooth operation when mounting or demounting a vehicle body frame;
Fig. 7 shows a schematic view of the position of various sensors which are used to provide control signals to the winch cable mechanism when mounting and demounting;
